<GlossaryTerm id="CDR0000045238"><TermName>photodynamic therapy</TermName><TermPronunciation>(FOH-toh-dy-NA-mik THAYR-uh-pee)</TermPronunciation><TermDefinition><DefinitionText>Treatment with drugs that become active when exposed to light. These activated drugs may kill cancer cells.</DefinitionText><Dictionary>Cancer.gov</Dictionary><Audience>Patient</Audience></TermDefinition><MediaLink ref="CDR0000705193" type="audio/mpeg" alt="Pronunciation of dictionary term &quot;photodynamic therapy&quot;" language="en" id="_3"/><MediaLink ref="CDR0000705192" type="audio/mpeg" alt="Pronunciation of dictionary term &quot;terapia fotodinámica&quot;" language="es" id="_4"/><SpanishTermName>terapia fotodinámica</SpanishTermName><SpanishTermDefinition><DefinitionText>Tratamiento con medicamentos que se vuelven activos cuando se exponen a la luz. Estos medicamentos destruyen las células cancerosas.</DefinitionText><Dictionary>Cancer.gov</Dictionary><Audience>Patient</Audience></SpanishTermDefinition><DateLastModified>2008-02-19</DateLastModified><RelatedInformation><RelatedExternalRef UseWith="en" xref="http://www.cancer.gov/about-cancer/treatment/types/surgery/photodynamic-fact-sheet">Photodynamic Therapy for Cancer</RelatedExternalRef><RelatedExternalRef UseWith="es" xref="http://www.cancer.gov/espanol/cancer/tratamiento/tipos/cirugia/hoja-informativa-terapia-fotodinamica">Terapia fotodinámica para el cáncer</RelatedExternalRef></RelatedInformation></GlossaryTerm>
